stylometry: The tradeoff is that if you produce too many of a product so that you have a lot of inventory on hand to meet demand, then your holding costs will spike up and you will be losing money on stagnent goods. But if you do not have enough inventory on hand in order to minimize holding costs and you get a spike in demand or a huge order then you will need to order in a big order thus spiking your production costs. So the dilemma is to find a way to be prepared for both and having enough inventory on hand so that you can minimize both costs and that is called aggregate planning.
